WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Eqwi' is a Workbench game where you try to remove all tiles
from a game board. To do this, you have to place tiles so that 3
tiles of the same type are following each other in a 'corridor'.
To complete a game board, you have to eliminate all tiles from one
corridor, including the tile located in the center of the game
board, which is indicated by a 'pressed down' space. When one
corridor is emptied, the remaining tiles from the other corridor
are eliminated and the game continues...

  Shown at the right of the game board are the next tiles that are
to be placed. The lowermost tile is the 'next tile' that will be
placed at the end of a series of tiles when you click inside a
corresponding corridor. If you click on the last tile of a series
in one corridor, that tile will be 'exchanged' with the next tile.
However, if that tile is of the same type as the next tile, the
next tile will be placed next to the clicked tile.

  One important thing to watch for is that the last tile of a
series of tiles must never reach the end of a corridor (indicated
by a dead-end space at the left or right in the game board)...
unless that tile is of the same type as the two tiles that precede
it, otherwise the game will be over.

  Have fun!

